text.section:
The bylaws shall contain provisions, consistent with this code, relating to:
The voting rights of members;
Election of directors, and the number, qualifications, terms of office and powers of directors;
Annual and special meetings of members;
The number, designation, election, terms and powers and duties of the respective corporate officers;
Deposit, custody, disbursement and accounting for corporate funds;
Fidelity bonds covering officers and employees of the insurer handling its funds, to be issued by the corporate surety and to be in such amount as may be reasonable; and
Such other matters as may be customary, necessary, or convenient for the management or regulation of corporate affairs.
